        <a id="main-content"></a>
            <h1 class="title" id="page-title">How to sort a column of a datagrid in VB.net</h1>                    <div class="region region-content">
  <section id="block-system-main" class="block block-system">

      
  <div class="content">
    
      
        
                    
              <p class="submitted"><span property="dc:date dc:created" content="2011-08-31T13:12:51+02:00" datatype="xsd:dateTime" rel="sioc:has_creator">Submitted by <span class="username" xml:lang="" about="/users/robert" typeof="sioc:UserAccount" property="foaf:name" datatype="">Robert</span> on Wed, 08/31/2011 - 13:12</span></p>
      
      
  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>Goal: This example shows you how to programmatically sort a column in a datagridview. </p>
<p>Instructions: Open a new Windows Forms Application and add 1 button and a datagridview to the form. Run the application and enter some data in column1. Then press the button to sort. Replace all the automatically generated code in your project with the code below. </p>
<p>Code: </p>
<p></p><div class="geshifilter"><pre class="vbnet geshifilter-vbnet" style="font-family:monospace;"><span style="color: #FF8000;">Public</span> <span style="color: #0600FF;">Class</span> Form1
 
    <span style="color: #FF8000;">Private</span> <span style="color: #0600FF;">Sub</span> Button1_Click<span style="color: #000000;">(</span><span style="color: #FF8000;">ByVal</span> sender <span style="color: #FF8000;">As</span> System.<span style="color: #FF0000;">Object</span>, <span style="color: #FF8000;">ByVal</span> e <span style="color: #FF8000;">As</span> System.<span style="color: #0000FF;">EventArgs</span><span style="color: #000000;">)</span> <span style="color: #FF8000;">Handles</span> Button1.<span style="color: #0000FF;">Click</span>
 
        <span style="color: #008080; font-style: italic;">' Sort first column, ascending:</span>
        DataGridView1.<span style="color: #0000FF;">Sort</span><span style="color: #000000;">(</span>DataGridView1.<span style="color: #0000FF;">Columns</span><span style="color: #000000;">(</span><span style="color: #FF0000;">0</span><span style="color: #000000;">)</span>, System.<span style="color: #0000FF;">ComponentModel</span>.<span style="color: #0000FF;">ListSortDirection</span>.<span style="color: #0000FF;">Ascending</span><span style="color: #000000;">)</span>
 
    <span style="color: #0600FF;">End</span> <span style="color: #0600FF;">Sub</span>
 
<span style="color: #0600FF;">End</span> <span style="color: #0600FF;">Class</span></pre></div>
</div></div></div>  </div>

